00:15:51.499 --> 00:15:52.709
So you got to kind of feel out the locals.

00:15:52.709 --> 00:15:54.220
Feel what they want to do.

00:15:54.220 --> 00:15:59.360
I find that having a group
and going with a group is helpful sometimes.

00:15:59.360 --> 00:16:00.670
Small
group.

00:16:00.670 --> 00:16:02.040
I've shot cities all by myself, too.

00:16:02.040 --> 00:16:05.079
I went to
Memphis, shot by myself, but went with on

00:16:05.079 --> 00:16:06.079
other guy.

00:16:06.079 --> 00:16:07.679
So
Sean Davis who's a local in Memphis and knows

00:16:07.679 --> 00:16:08.679
a lot about
it.

00:16:08.679 --> 00:16:10.079
He knew a lot of spots.

00:16:10.079 --> 00:16:12.839
On top of the Peabody Hotel.

00:16:12.839 --> 00:16:16.019
Speaking of hotels before you
go -- I like to look at where are all the

00:16:16.019 --> 00:16:17.019
view spots?

00:16:17.019 --> 00:16:19.290
Where can you get up high in the city?

00:16:19.290 --> 00:16:20.660
So do a little
bit of research.

00:16:20.660 --> 00:16:21.709
Is there a bar?

00:16:21.709 --> 00:16:25.699
In San Francisco, our own city up here, you
can get to the top of the Marriott; there's

00:16:25.699 --> 00:16:26.699
a great view from up there.

00:16:26.699 --> 00:16:27.699
They have a bar up there.

00:16:27.699 --> 00:16:32.189
There are some places you can get on top of
the Mandarin

00:16:32.189 --> 00:16:34.079
Hotel in San Francisco.

00:16:34.079 --> 00:16:37.290
Which has a wonderful view down
on the TransAmerica building.

00:16:37.290 --> 00:16:40.160
So hotels are also great
for getting on the top of because a lot of

00:16:40.160 --> 00:16:41.550
times you can get
into a hotel.

00:16:41.550 --> 00:16:44.300
It's not like an office building where they've
got security and everything.

00:16:44.300 --> 00:16:46.480
And you can frequently find
your way onto a roof.

00:16:46.480 --> 00:16:50.699
I find -- I know this sounds
crazy.

00:16:50.699 --> 00:16:54.340
I find 50, 60 times and yes, you're probably
technically trespassing and all that, but

00:16:54.340 --> 00:16:58.630
50, 60 percent
of the time you can get on most hotel roofs

00:16:58.630 --> 00:17:04.709
and those are some
great places to take shots.

00:17:04.709 --> 00:17:08.760
We'll do some of those from
the roofs and stuff sometimes.

00:17:08.760 --> 00:17:13.679
I think if I do go to a city and do
a photo walk and I do a lot of photo walks.

00:17:13.679 --> 00:17:20.579
I've
probably done 125 photo walks.

00:17:20.579 --> 00:17:25.390
I'll go and schedule that
if it's a big photo walk for one night for

00:17:25.390 --> 00:17:26.750
like three or
four hours.

00:17:26.750 --> 00:17:31.380
Because it's really hard on big photo walks
to really focus on shooting a city.

00:17:31.380 --> 00:17:33.130
You can't shoot it; they're more of a social
thing.

00:17:33.130 --> 00:17:36.450
But if I do a photo walk in a city, but if
you get too many people?

00:17:36.450 --> 00:17:39.560
We went on a
trip to Boston with some friends from Flickr

00:17:39.560 --> 00:17:40.640
and there
were probably 20 people.

00:17:40.640 --> 00:17:41.640
It was too big.

00:17:41.640 --> 00:17:42.640
It was too many.

00:17:42.640 --> 00:17:43.830
You can't keep track of
everybody.

00:17:43.830 --> 00:17:45.419
You kind of lose people.

00:17:45.419 --> 00:17:48.990
So I think -- but I
think planning the trip, having everything,

00:17:48.990 --> 00:17:51.640
having a
route, having everything on Google map before

00:17:51.640 --> 00:17:52.640
you go.

00:17:52.640 --> 00:17:56.380
When I am there, there's no time to be online.

00:17:56.380 --> 00:17:58.250
You know,
I'm not going to be socializing.

00:17:58.250 --> 00:17:59.710
I got to focus on
shooting.

00:17:59.710 --> 00:18:01.049
I'm not going to be processing.

00:18:01.049 --> 00:18:02.960
You have to
resist the urge to process.

00:18:02.960 --> 00:18:04.010
You just took all these
great shots.

00:18:04.010 --> 00:18:05.510
And you're like oh, I just got a sunrise.

00:18:05.510 --> 00:18:07.809
I want to process it get it online.

00:18:07.809 --> 00:18:08.809
It's so cool.

00:18:08.809 --> 00:18:09.809
I want to do it right now.

00:18:09.809 --> 00:18:10.809
You
can't.

00:18:10.809 --> 00:18:13.179
You got to focus shoot, shoot, shoot, shoot,
shoot, shoot.

00:18:13.179 --> 00:18:15.420
There
will be time for that later.

00:18:15.420 --> 00:18:18.289
I know in Death Valley it
was like oh boy we just shot this Racetrack.

00:18:18.289 --> 00:18:20.500
I
want to process them.

00:18:20.500 --> 00:18:21.500
Resist the temptation.

00:18:21.500 --> 00:18:33.420
I think
[pause] Oh, one of the other things I do if

00:18:33.420 --> 00:18:36.020
I'm driving
and I have my route in addition to having

00:18:36.020 --> 00:18:39.440
it on a map and
on the phone I actually print it out and print

00:18:39.440 --> 00:18:41.900
it by the
address in order of what I'm going to shoot.

00:18:41.900 --> 00:18:43.500
So I
actually have a printout.

00:18:43.500 --> 00:18:47.770
In case all of a sudden you wont' be able
to connect on the internet or something happens

00:18:47.770 --> 00:18:48.770
and you can't get it.

00:18:48.770 --> 00:18:55.120
I think having a printout helps as well.

00:18:55.120 --> 00:18:57.910
I think considering bundling trips
is also a great way to do it.

00:18:57.910 --> 00:19:00.309
I'll shoot Nashville and
Memphis.

00:19:00.309 --> 00:19:01.890
Austin and Houston.

00:19:01.890 --> 00:19:09.560
Cities that are close
together to try to maximize the travel time.

00:19:09.560 --> 00:19:13.750
As far as
post processing goes, you know, that's a big

00:19:13.750 --> 00:19:14.799
part of it.

00:19:14.799 --> 00:19:18.020
I use Lightroom to process my photos but I
don't have a

00:19:18.020 --> 00:19:19.519
lot of time.

00:19:19.519 --> 00:19:21.840
You have to go very, very quickly.

00:19:21.840 --> 00:19:23.850
If I'm
going to publish a million photos, my goal

00:19:23.850 --> 00:19:28.019
is I have to
process at least 350 photos a week.

00:19:28.019 --> 00:19:30.789
And if I'm gone the
weekend before because I'm doing a shoot,

00:19:30.789 --> 00:19:32.930
that means 700 the next weekend.

00:19:32.930 --> 00:19:34.960
So you got
to power through them and you can't spend

00:19:34.960 --> 00:19:37.840
more than a
couple minutes on a shot.

